message: "If you use this benchmark, data, or report, please cite it as below."
title: "Distilled Vertical Prompts for Efficient STEM Reasoning: Cheap Models Match Frontier Accuracy on Hebrew RTL Problems at a Fraction of the Cost"
abstract: >-
  An independent technical research report and reproducible benchmark. Eight LLMs across three cost
  tiers are evaluated on an original, self-contained Hebrew (RTL) STEM corpus (mechanics,
  electromagnetism, linear algebra, calculus, discrete mathematics) under three prompt levels and
  zero-shot vs. RAG (720 blind-graded cells). Accuracy is near-ceiling and prompt lift is ~0; the
  differentiator is cost per correct answer, where a Tier-3 open model matches frontier accuracy at
  roughly 117x lower cost than a frontier model.
type: dataset
